# Live preview → everywhere else

Whenever you change something that **affects how the live preview displays** a slide (or what data it uses), you must **update every other code path** that renders the same slide for users. Do not ship a feature only in `SlidePreview` or only in export.

Treat “live preview” as the **editor `SlidePreview`** (e.g. in `SlideEditForm`) and any **read-only `SlidePreview`** that shows the same slide model.

## What counts as “affects the preview”

Examples (not exhaustive):

- Layout, text zones, alignment, max lines, rotation
- Fonts, sizes, highlights, outlines, bold weights, spans
- Background: solid/gradient/pattern/image, multi-image, PiP, focal point, frame, rotation
- Chrome: counter, watermark, **swipe hint**, “Made with”, positions/sizes/colors
- Overlays, tints, safe areas, bordered frame
- Normalization of `slide.meta` / template defaults / `background` JSON
- Anything that changes **pixels** or **meaningful positioning** on the canvas

If unsure, assume it must propagate.

## Surfaces to keep in sync

After a preview-affecting change, verify and update as needed:

1. **Live preview** — `SlidePreview` usage in the editor (`SlideEditForm`, etc.): props, overrides, normalization.
2. **Export & downloads** — Server HTML/image pipelines: `lib/server/renderer/renderSlideHtml.ts`, routes under `app/api/export/**`, and any job that builds slide images or PDFs.
3. **Render / thumbnail APIs** — e.g. `app/api/render/slide/[slideId]` (iframes, list thumbnails): same meta, background URL resolution, chrome, and dimensions as the carousel export size.
4. **Carousel page** — `p/[projectId]/c/[carouselId]`: `SlideGrid` / `SlidePreview` must get the same overrides, signed URLs, and normalization as the editor.
5. **Per-slide editor route** — `c/[carouselId]/s/[slideId]`: initial image URLs and chrome should match list/editor behavior.
6. **Template UI** — Template picker cards, template builder, `SlideEditorModal`, etc.: anything using `SlidePreview` or template config must support the same options (`getOverridesFromConfig`, zone/chrome overrides).
7. **Video / compositing** — `render-for-video`, transparent/background-only modes if your change touches layers they depend on.

## Checklist (use before finishing a task)

- [ ] **Editor preview** uses the new behavior and data.
- [ ] **`renderSlideHtml`** (and export routes) apply the same rules and normalized meta.
- [ ] **Carousel grid / slide list thumbnails** pass the same overrides and URL resolution.
- [ ] **Template modals / cards** still match when relevant.
- [ ] **`pnpm run build`** passes (see `01-run-build-after-changes.mdc`).

## Anti-patterns

- Implementing a visual feature only in the client preview.
- Divergent background signing or `storage_path` handling between the carousel page and `/api/render/slide`.
- Different chrome rules (e.g. swipe `swipe_x` / `swipe_y`) between `SlidePreview` and `renderSlideHtml`.

When adding shared logic, prefer a **single normalization or resolver** used by both client preview inputs and server render, rather than duplicating conditionals in four places.
